<p>I have an HTML page with a heading and 2 Divs, I then have a javascript where I want the heading to change if the user selects one off the Divs.</p>  <p><a href="https://jsfiddle.net/L27xqgfs/1/" rel="nofollow">https://jsfiddle.net/L27xqgfs/1/</a></p>  <pre><code>var happyMood = getElementById("happy"); var sadMood = getElementById("sad");   happyMood.onclick = function () {     var mainHeading = getElementById("heading");     mainHeading.innerHTML = "You have selected ";  };  sadMood.onclick = function () {     var mainHeading = getElementById("heading");     mainHeading.innerHTML = "You have selected " + sadMood; }; </code></pre>  <p>Please can someone advise where I've gone wrong?</p>  <p>Thanks in advance.</p>